[Episode 22]

3
00:01:39,180 --> 00:01:39,820
Look.

4
00:01:41,150 --> 00:01:42,030
This is it.

5
00:01:47,759 --> 00:01:48,910
Do you still remember which company

6
00:01:49,150 --> 00:01:50,950
the rickshaw belonged to

7
00:01:50,979 --> 00:01:51,979
when you came back?

8
00:01:55,910 --> 00:01:56,789
No.

9
00:01:59,880 --> 00:02:02,470
[Military Hospital]

10
00:02:02,830 --> 00:02:03,310
Go and find

11
00:02:03,310 --> 00:02:05,070
Mi Lan's former classmates

12
00:02:05,070 --> 00:02:05,910
and teachers from nursing school.

13
00:02:06,630 --> 00:02:08,190
Use her current photo to confirm

14
00:02:08,210 --> 00:02:09,289
if she's the same person.

15
00:02:09,830 --> 00:02:10,340
If she is,

16
00:02:10,370 --> 00:02:11,240
dig deeper.

17
00:02:11,650 --> 00:02:13,370
Look into her past—

18
00:02:13,550 --> 00:02:15,510
find out if she had any unusual experiences

19
00:02:15,710 --> 00:02:16,350
or connections with specific individuals.

20
00:02:16,470 --> 00:02:17,270
The more detailed, the better.

21
00:02:17,390 --> 00:02:18,710
You suspect she's the killer?

22
00:02:18,900 --> 00:02:20,510
This woman has always made me uneasy.

23
00:02:21,220 --> 00:02:22,720
After what happened this time,

24
00:02:23,140 --> 00:02:24,660
it has only strengthened my suspicions.

25
00:02:25,070 --> 00:02:25,840
This woman

26
00:02:26,110 --> 00:02:27,680
is definitely not just a nurse.

27
00:02:30,990 --> 00:02:31,829
I understand.

28
00:02:32,310 --> 00:02:34,230
That's why you tapped her phone

29
00:02:34,290 --> 00:02:36,280
and placed surveillance near her home.

30
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:38,430
Track down the rickshaw driver

31
00:02:38,450 --> 00:02:39,270
who took Mi Lan back to the Military Hospital.

32
00:02:39,430 --> 00:02:40,510
Bring him to me.

33
00:02:40,990 --> 00:02:42,230
Until I see him,

34
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:43,790
make sure no one else contacts him.

35
00:02:44,140 --> 00:02:44,750
Yes.

36
00:02:58,320 --> 00:03:00,380
Niu Erhong's entire family moved out overnight.

37
00:03:00,410 --> 00:03:02,050
They didn't even pack properly

38
00:03:02,220 --> 00:03:04,160
and didn't inform anyone.

39
00:03:04,190 --> 00:03:05,150
Definitely suspicious.

40
00:03:05,310 --> 00:03:06,150
Take a look at this, sir.

41
00:03:08,240 --> 00:03:09,830
I did instruct Li Liang

42
00:03:10,030 --> 00:03:11,400
to routinely track and monitor

43
00:03:11,430 --> 00:03:12,980
officers at the division level—

44
00:03:13,100 --> 00:03:15,540
that's part of our standard procedures.

45
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:16,590
I didn't report it to you

46
00:03:16,790 --> 00:03:18,070
but look at these photos.

47
00:03:18,430 --> 00:03:20,510
I didn't authorize Li Liang to take these,

48
00:03:20,870 --> 00:03:22,350
and they definitely weren't taken by him.

49
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:24,680
Chinese calligraphy follows rules of horizontal and vertical alignment,

50
00:03:24,710 --> 00:03:26,750
and each character has a set form.

51
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:29,200
But individual handwriting styles vary,

52
00:03:29,230 --> 00:03:31,430
which is the basis for handwriting analysis.

53
00:03:31,550 --> 00:03:32,579
It's the same with photography.

54
00:03:33,290 --> 00:03:34,360
Different photographers

55
00:03:34,390 --> 00:03:36,550
have distinct styles and perspectives.

56
00:03:36,870 --> 00:03:38,030
Look at this photo—

57
00:03:38,630 --> 00:03:39,829
it's one Li Liang took.

58
00:03:40,270 --> 00:03:41,550
Now compare it to this one.

59
00:03:43,350 --> 00:03:45,790
If you examine closely, you'll see

60
00:03:46,040 --> 00:03:46,760
these were

61
00:03:46,790 --> 00:03:48,590
clearly taken by two different people.

62
00:03:50,230 --> 00:03:50,950
Indeed.

63
00:03:51,760 --> 00:03:53,760
Photos taken by a trained agent are distinct

64
00:03:53,790 --> 00:03:55,520
from those taken by an ordinary person.

65
00:03:56,390 --> 00:03:58,230
It seems you and Yun Hongshen are on the same page.

66
00:03:58,760 --> 00:04:00,440
If the photo he found

67
00:04:00,470 --> 00:04:01,230
hadn't been destroyed,

68
00:04:01,350 --> 00:04:03,310
we might've uncovered more clues.

69
00:04:04,430 --> 00:04:06,300
We still don't know who the photographer is,

70
00:04:06,320 --> 00:04:07,200
but I believe

71
00:04:07,230 --> 00:04:08,510
if we investigate further,

72
00:04:08,860 --> 00:04:10,260
they're bound to slip up.

73
00:04:10,960 --> 00:04:12,280
Who else had access

74
00:04:12,310 --> 00:04:13,400
to Yun Hongshen's last photo?

75
00:04:13,470 --> 00:04:14,510
You, me,

76
00:04:14,590 --> 00:04:15,510
and a few division chiefs.

77
00:04:17,740 --> 00:04:18,579
It seems the mole

78
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:20,370
is among us.

79
00:04:21,630 --> 00:04:22,150
That's right.

80
00:04:22,350 --> 00:04:23,710
Each of them is capable.

81
00:04:23,950 --> 00:04:25,280
Qu Wenzhi's defection,

82
00:04:25,310 --> 00:04:26,950
along with the subsequent events,

83
00:04:27,350 --> 00:04:29,110
ties back to them in varying degrees.

84
00:04:30,270 --> 00:04:31,310
Who do you suspect more?

85
00:04:33,630 --> 00:04:34,510
Does Ling Han seem likely?

86
00:04:35,430 --> 00:04:35,750
Chief,

87
00:04:35,750 --> 00:04:37,670
I don't have a particular inclination right now.

88
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:38,350
Honestly,

89
00:04:38,670 --> 00:04:40,030
it doesn't matter who seems likely.

90
00:04:40,060 --> 00:04:41,909
What's critical is solid evidence.

91
00:04:42,070 --> 00:04:44,310
Ling Han has been particularly aggressive in his recent work.

92
00:04:44,390 --> 00:04:45,510
I have my reservations about him,

93
00:04:45,630 --> 00:04:48,150
but that doesn't necessarily make him the mole.

94
00:04:48,310 --> 00:04:50,630
Also, I believe the tension between us

95
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:52,710
is likely part of the mole's strategy.

96
00:04:58,310 --> 00:04:59,030
Zhu,

97
00:04:59,550 --> 00:05:01,470
as always, your thinking is sharp.

98
00:05:02,510 --> 00:05:03,670
Ling Han may be clever,

99
00:05:03,870 --> 00:05:05,310
but he's not steady enough in his actions.

100
00:05:06,150 --> 00:05:06,830
Zhu,

101
00:05:07,710 --> 00:05:09,470
I'm sorry this situation has caused you trouble.

102
00:05:10,130 --> 00:05:11,290
Chief, it's nothing.

103
00:05:11,630 --> 00:05:14,030
We all encounter unpleasant situations.

104
00:05:14,240 --> 00:05:17,440
If we took everything to heart,

105
00:05:17,550 --> 00:05:19,150
we couldn't do this job.

106
00:05:20,150 --> 00:05:21,350
That's the mindset of a true Deputy Chief—

107
00:05:22,190 --> 00:05:22,950
admirable.

108
00:05:25,680 --> 00:05:26,310
What's the matter?

109
00:05:27,710 --> 00:05:28,310
Chief,

110
00:05:29,550 --> 00:05:32,430
what do you think of leveraging

111
00:05:32,950 --> 00:05:34,750
Yun Hongshen's informant in Shanghai?

112
00:05:37,130 --> 00:05:38,130
Stirring up the situation

113
00:05:38,430 --> 00:05:40,350
might actually be part of the mole's plan.

114
00:05:40,710 --> 00:05:42,950
The more confusing things appear,

115
00:05:43,250 --> 00:05:45,530
the harder it will be for you to pinpoint the mole.

116
00:05:46,020 --> 00:05:46,950
There's another way

117
00:05:47,280 --> 00:05:48,720
to identify the mole:

118
00:05:48,750 --> 00:05:49,550
they'll definitely

119
00:05:50,950 --> 00:05:51,710
be interested in

120
00:05:51,750 --> 00:05:53,870
Yun Hongshen's mysterious informant.

121
00:05:55,500 --> 00:05:57,020
That's a good point.

122
00:05:59,720 --> 00:06:00,270
You see?

123
00:06:00,630 --> 00:06:01,640
That guy's definitely hiding something.

124
00:06:01,830 --> 00:06:02,630
I think we should interrogate him again.

125
00:06:03,750 --> 00:06:04,150
Let's go.

126
00:06:08,430 --> 00:06:11,070
Whether or not this was orchestrated by Gui,

127
00:06:11,510 --> 00:06:13,270
this time Happy House is finished.

128
00:06:14,590 --> 00:06:15,310
Think about it—

129
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:17,470
the victim was Old Master Yun's widow,

130
00:06:17,820 --> 00:06:19,100
and she died so gruesomely.

131
00:06:19,830 --> 00:06:21,750
Do you think Old Master Yun's

132
00:06:22,100 --> 00:06:23,680
prominent students will let this slide?

133
00:06:25,270 --> 00:06:26,070
I think even if

134
00:06:26,410 --> 00:06:28,680
Happy House doesn't go under completely, it'll take a huge hit.

135
00:06:29,030 --> 00:06:32,350
There has to be a scapegoat to satisfy the authorities' anger.

136
00:06:33,230 --> 00:06:33,710
Indeed.

137
00:06:34,490 --> 00:06:36,409
Until this case is resolved,

138
00:06:36,610 --> 00:06:38,120
there's no way Happy House can reopen.

139
00:06:39,510 --> 00:06:40,350
And those who were

140
00:06:40,370 --> 00:06:41,570
in business with Bai Qingkui?

141
00:06:42,030 --> 00:06:43,380
They'll likely suffer too.

142
00:06:43,780 --> 00:06:45,100
I think the Bai Clan and Happy House

143
00:06:45,159 --> 00:06:47,120
are about to become history.

144
00:06:48,070 --> 00:06:48,750
True.

145
00:06:51,470 --> 00:06:51,950
Captain Tang.

146
00:06:52,350 --> 00:06:53,070
I have some business to attend to.

147
00:06:53,270 --> 00:06:53,870
You go ahead with your work.

148
00:07:01,970 --> 00:07:02,690
Captain Tang.

149
00:07:03,470 --> 00:07:04,190
Brother-in-law,

150
00:07:04,390 --> 00:07:05,670
I swear it wasn't me.

151
00:07:05,790 --> 00:07:06,870
I swear to the heavens!

152
00:07:07,280 --> 00:07:08,550
I really want to help you,

153
00:07:08,670 --> 00:07:09,870
but this case isn't under my jurisdiction.

154
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:11,120
I can't intervene.

155
00:07:11,150 --> 00:07:12,560
If you truly wanted to help,

156
00:07:12,590 --> 00:07:13,750
you could always find a way.

157
00:07:13,950 --> 00:07:14,550
Brother-in-law.

158
00:07:15,190 --> 00:07:15,870
brother-in-law.

159
00:07:16,950 --> 00:07:18,830
We're in the same boat now.

160
00:07:19,110 --> 00:07:20,510
If I go down,

161
00:07:20,550 --> 00:07:21,830
it won't look good for you either.

162
00:07:23,750 --> 00:07:24,780
What are you implying?

163
00:07:24,950 --> 00:07:26,550
Who's in the same boat as you?

164
00:07:26,750 --> 00:07:27,710
I mean...

165
00:07:27,950 --> 00:07:28,550
Captain,

166
00:07:29,310 --> 00:07:29,920
the Director needs to see you.

167
00:07:29,940 --> 00:07:30,950
Seems urgent.

168
00:07:30,980 --> 00:07:31,830
You should go over there.

169
00:07:32,190 --> 00:07:32,590
Alright.

170
00:07:34,150 --> 00:07:34,800
I have something to attend to.

171
00:07:34,830 --> 00:07:35,670
We'll discuss this matter later.

172
00:07:36,510 --> 00:07:37,240
Brother-in-law!

173
00:07:37,430 --> 00:07:38,080
I think even if

174
00:07:38,110 --> 00:07:40,350
Happy House doesn't go under completely, it'll take a huge hit.

175
00:07:40,390 --> 00:07:40,909
True.

176
00:07:41,030 --> 00:07:42,990
至少在这件事情调查清楚之前

177
00:07:43,150 --> 00:07:44,670
there's no way Happy House can reopen.

178
00:07:44,850 --> 00:07:45,760
And those who were

179
00:07:45,790 --> 00:07:46,909
in business with Bai Qingkui?

180
00:07:47,350 --> 00:07:48,710
They'll likely suffer too.

181
00:08:09,350 --> 00:08:10,070
Mengying.

182
00:08:11,870 --> 00:08:13,150
Why are you here at this hour?

183
00:08:13,430 --> 00:08:15,270
Is it because you feel uneasy being alone?

184
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:16,710
Come in, quickly.

185
00:08:25,510 --> 00:08:26,750
Have a seat.

186
00:08:26,910 --> 00:08:27,860
Why are you just standing there?

187
00:08:30,990 --> 00:08:32,450
Isn't it time for the old lady's medicine?

188
00:08:32,990 --> 00:08:33,539
No rush.

189
00:08:33,669 --> 00:08:35,070
It still needs to cool for another half hour.

190
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:36,870
Here, have some water.

191
00:08:41,750 --> 00:08:43,270
You look so pale. What's wrong?

192
00:08:44,080 --> 00:08:45,630
Madam Yun has been poisoned to death.

193
00:08:45,860 --> 00:08:47,300
The NBIS suspects it was me.

194
00:08:47,870 --> 00:08:49,620
They want to shut down Happy House.

195
00:08:50,430 --> 00:08:52,630
Master's lifetime of effort will be wasted.

196
00:08:53,110 --> 00:08:53,790
Mengying,

197
00:08:54,520 --> 00:08:55,930
I swear on my life.

198
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:57,390
It wasn't me!

199
00:08:57,630 --> 00:08:59,030
Who would be so vile?

200
00:08:59,350 --> 00:09:01,150
Old Madam Yun was such a kind person.

201
00:09:02,030 --> 00:09:03,510
Whoever poisoned her

202
00:09:03,630 --> 00:09:04,830
is sure to get their comeuppance!

203
00:09:05,550 --> 00:09:06,150
Jin Gui,

204
00:09:06,270 --> 00:09:07,030
don't worry.

205
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:08,340
When Tang comes back,

206
00:09:08,550 --> 00:09:09,950
I'll ask him to figure something out for you.

207
00:09:10,350 --> 00:09:11,110
Rest assured.

208
00:09:11,430 --> 00:09:12,750
You didn't do it,

209
00:09:12,950 --> 00:09:14,070
so there's nothing to fear.

210
00:09:17,710 --> 00:09:18,270
Mengying.

211
00:09:18,870 --> 00:09:19,830
Captain Tang

212
00:09:20,390 --> 00:09:22,350
has to shoulder it with me.

213
00:09:25,550 --> 00:09:27,150
Listen to yourself.

214
00:09:27,910 --> 00:09:29,270
When you run into trouble,

215
00:09:29,390 --> 00:09:30,350
Tang helps out—

216
00:09:30,480 --> 00:09:31,440
that's for the sake of

217
00:09:31,470 --> 00:09:32,670
the bond we've built over the years.

218
00:09:33,110 --> 00:09:34,550
But asking him to bear the blame with you?

219
00:09:34,990 --> 00:09:36,550
That's going too far.

220
00:09:37,390 --> 00:09:39,950
I'm the real owner of Zhang's pharmacy.

221
00:09:41,510 --> 00:09:42,390
What?

222
00:09:43,210 --> 00:09:44,850
Are you two acting together to fool me?

223
00:09:49,870 --> 00:09:50,990
Was that incident before

224
00:09:51,120 --> 00:09:53,710
all part of a trap you set to trick me?

225
00:09:54,350 --> 00:09:55,020
Yes.

226
00:09:56,220 --> 00:09:57,390
Jin Gui, are you even human?

227
00:09:57,590 --> 00:09:58,830
You even set me up?

228
00:09:59,150 --> 00:10:00,390
Let me tell you the truth.

229
00:10:00,510 --> 00:10:01,790
I tampered with

230
00:10:01,910 --> 00:10:03,150
the documents you signed.

231
00:10:03,670 --> 00:10:05,470
What you invested in wasn't Zhang's pharmacy—

232
00:10:05,780 --> 00:10:06,820
it was Happy House.

233
00:10:13,910 --> 00:10:14,910
Why would you do this?

234
00:10:15,920 --> 00:10:18,060
To have leverage over Captain Tang.

235
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:20,210
Something to save myself when it counts.

236
00:10:21,270 --> 00:10:21,870
And look—

237
00:10:22,310 --> 00:10:23,660
it's coming in handy now.

238
00:10:26,870 --> 00:10:27,910
You lunatic!

239
00:10:28,870 --> 00:10:30,350
Tang hasn't wronged you.

240
00:10:30,790 --> 00:10:32,110
Are you trying to destroy him?

241
00:10:34,580 --> 00:10:35,670
Mengying,

242
00:10:35,950 --> 00:10:37,550
what's wrong?

243
00:10:37,970 --> 00:10:38,790
Mom, it's nothing.

244
00:10:42,910 --> 00:10:48,240
[Changsha Police Station]

245
00:10:47,790 --> 00:10:48,350
Mrs. Tang.

246
00:10:48,510 --> 00:10:49,150
You were looking for me?

247
00:10:49,190 --> 00:10:49,990
What's the matter?

248
00:10:50,470 --> 00:10:51,150
Huang,

249
00:10:51,310 --> 00:10:52,390
let me ask you something.

250
00:10:52,660 --> 00:10:54,690
Is Happy House doomed?

251
00:10:56,120 --> 00:10:56,960
Is there no hope for recovery?

252
00:10:57,470 --> 00:10:58,030
Mrs. Tang,

253
00:10:58,640 --> 00:11:00,520
I know about your connection with Mrs. Jin.

254
00:11:01,270 --> 00:11:02,150
But let me warn you—

255
00:11:02,540 --> 00:11:03,670
stay out of this.

256
00:11:04,140 --> 00:11:05,230
Anyone who gets involved will suffer for it.

257
00:11:08,350 --> 00:11:11,870
Did a high-ranking official of Changsha

258
00:11:12,360 --> 00:11:13,920
flee to Shanghai to become a traitor?

259
00:11:14,310 --> 00:11:15,780
Don't even mention that.

260
00:11:15,870 --> 00:11:17,110
The NBIS is investigating it.

261
00:11:20,630 --> 00:11:21,190
And that incident

262
00:11:21,270 --> 00:11:22,550
is linked to Happy House.

263
00:11:22,990 --> 00:11:25,190
All those who had dealings with Happy House

264
00:11:25,270 --> 00:11:26,460
are avoiding it like the plague,

265
00:11:26,910 --> 00:11:28,110
afraid of being implicated.

266
00:11:29,190 --> 00:11:29,860
Jin Gui...

267
00:11:30,070 --> 00:11:31,870
If Jin Gui turns herself in,

268
00:11:32,330 --> 00:11:33,940
can she save Happy House?

269
00:11:34,780 --> 00:11:37,610
That depends on what she's willing to reveal.

270
00:11:38,580 --> 00:11:40,060
If she spills something big enough,

271
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:41,900
not only could Happy House survive,

272
00:11:42,150 --> 00:11:42,990
it might even

273
00:11:43,270 --> 00:11:44,470
thrive in the future—

274
00:11:44,510 --> 00:11:45,350
make a fortune.

275
00:11:45,710 --> 00:11:47,510
What counts as something big?

276
00:11:49,990 --> 00:11:50,830
For example,

277
00:11:52,300 --> 00:11:54,180
who helped that official escape?

278
00:11:58,780 --> 00:11:59,470
Mrs. Tang.

279
00:11:59,670 --> 00:12:00,310
Mrs. Tang.

280
00:12:00,430 --> 00:12:01,470
Are you alright, Mrs. Tang?

281
00:12:02,750 --> 00:12:04,350
Why don't you come in and have some water?

282
00:12:05,870 --> 00:12:06,670
I'm fine.

283
00:12:08,070 --> 00:12:08,990
I'm fine.

284
00:12:10,390 --> 00:12:11,190
Oh, and listen—

285
00:12:11,350 --> 00:12:11,910
don't tell Tang

286
00:12:12,020 --> 00:12:14,110
anything about me

287
00:12:14,550 --> 00:12:16,070
coming to see you.

288
00:12:16,470 --> 00:12:17,470
Promise me, you won't tell him.

